            Feedbacks
**********************************************-->
<setup>
  <select name="correctFeedback" type="text">
    <option>Awesome!</option>
    <option>Great job!</option>
    <option>Fantastic!</option>
    <option>Nice work!</option>
    <option>Amazing!</option>
    <option>Excellent!</option>
    <option>Right on!</option>
    <option>Perfect!</option>
  </select>
</setup>
  <feedback condition="$correct">$correctFeedback</feedback>
  
  <feedback condition="$ans8.numSubmissions > 2 and $ans8.creditAchieved != 1">
     <div name="helpText">
      Recall that the number of ways to choose <m>k</m> objects, without order, from a set of <m>n</m> objects, is the number of <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-1-5/"><term>combinations</term></ref>, given by: 
       <me>C(n,k) = \binom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}.</me>
       In contrast, the number of ways to choose <m>k</m> objects <em>in a certain order</em>, is the number of <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-1-4/"><term>permutations</term></ref>, given by: 
    <me>P(n,k) = \frac{n!}{(n-k)!}.</me>
       In this example, the people are being seated from left to right, so the order <em>does</em> matter.
    </div>
  </feedback>



<!--*********************************************
            Hint
**********************************************-->
<hint name="helpSection"><title>Worked Example</title>



<p>Here is a similar worked example:</p> 
<example newNameSpace>
<setup>
  <math name="n">15</math>
  <math name="k">7</math>
  <math name="permutekOfN" simplify>$n!/($n - $k)!</math>
</setup>

  
<p><em>From a group of <m>$n</m> people, in how many ways can <m>$k</m> people be seated in a row, from left to right?</em></p> 

<p><alert><em>Solution.</em></alert></p>
<p>Use the formula for <m>P(n,k)</m>
      <md>
        <mrow>P(n,k) \amp= \frac{n!}{(n-k)!} \amp\text{general formula}</mrow>
        <mrow>P($n,$k) \amp= \frac{$n!}{($n-$k)!} \amp\text{substitute}</mrow>
        <mrow> \amp= $permutekOfN \amp\text{evaluate}</mrow>
      </md></p>
  
</example>

</hint>

<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->  
<solution>
<p>Use the formula for <m>P(n,k)</m>
      <md>
        <mrow>P(n,k) \amp= \frac{n!}{(n-k)!} \amp\text{general formula}</mrow>
        <mrow>P($n,$k) \amp= \frac{$n!}{($n-$k)!} \amp\text{substitute}</mrow>
        <mrow> \amp= $permutekOfN{simplify} \amp\text{evaluate}</mrow>
      </md></p>

</solution>
</problem>



